This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on October 17, 2014, provides an order of succession within the Social Security Administration (SSA). The memorandum states that in the event that both the Commissioner and Deputy Commissioner of Social Security are unable to perform their duties, the following officials of the SSA will act as and perform the functions and duties of the Commissioner: Deputy Commissioner for Operations, Deputy Commissioner for Budget, Finance, Quality, and Management, Deputy Commissioner for Systems, Regional Commissioner (Atlanta), and Regional Commissioner (Dallas). The memorandum also states that certain exceptions apply, and the President retains the discretion to depart from this order of succession. Additionally, the memorandum revokes a previous Presidential Memorandum issued on October 17, 2008, and includes general provisions stating that it does not create any legally enforceable rights or benefits.